1028
01:05:30,500 --> 01:05:33,500
It hurts so bad! Please!

1029
01:05:41,400 --> 01:05:42,900
It hurts so bad!

1030
01:05:43,000 --> 01:05:44,900
Block it up here.

1031
01:05:45,000 --> 01:05:47,100
Get me some more bags!

1032
01:05:48,100 --> 01:05:50,700
Did we get 'em?
Did we get 'em all?

1033
01:05:51,700 --> 01:05:53,400
She was right.

1034
01:05:53,500 --> 01:05:55,800
She said that it would happen like this.

1035
01:05:55,900 --> 01:05:57,900
She said that
they would come at night.

1036
01:05:59,100 --> 01:06:00,900
She told us someone would die.

1037
01:06:24,900 --> 01:06:26,600
Mommy.

1038
01:06:28,200 --> 01:06:30,200
Ohh, shh, shh, shh.
It's okay.

1039
01:06:31,300 --> 01:06:33,000
It's okay, it was just a dream.

1040
01:06:34,000 --> 01:06:35,300
It's just a bad dream.

1041
01:06:36,400 --> 01:06:38,100
I want my mommy.

1042
01:06:38,200 --> 01:06:39,800
I know.

1043
01:06:39,900 --> 01:06:42,100
I know. Of course you do.

1044
01:06:42,200 --> 01:06:44,800
- Shh.
- I wanna go home.

1045
01:06:44,900 --> 01:06:46,400
Just sleep.

1046
01:06:47,700 --> 01:06:49,400
Everything'll be better in the morning.

1047
01:06:56,100 --> 01:06:57,600
Think he likes you.

1048
01:07:00,100 --> 01:07:02,700
Well, I hate that
I had to lie to him.

1049
01:07:03,800 --> 01:07:05,200
You have kids?

1050
01:07:05,300 --> 01:07:06,500
No.

1051
01:07:06,600 --> 01:07:08,800
I always wanted to, but...

1052
01:07:09,800 --> 01:07:11,500
things haven't been working out.

1053
01:07:13,800 --> 01:07:16,800
Right now I'm thinking
maybe that's for the best.

1054
01:07:18,000 --> 01:07:21,800
I saw creatures
fly into the store tonight that...

1055
01:07:21,900 --> 01:07:23,600
they shouldn't exist.

1056
01:07:25,000 --> 01:07:27,600
I keep thinking I'm gonna
wake up in a rubber room.

1057
01:07:29,000 --> 01:07:30,300
You're not alone in that.

1058
01:07:31,300 --> 01:07:32,800
We're all right there with you.

1059
01:07:33,900 --> 01:07:35,700
This isn't gonna end, is it?

1060
01:07:38,700 --> 01:07:39,700
David.

1061
01:07:40,700 --> 01:07:43,000
It's Joe. He's getting worse.

1062
01:08:00,900 --> 01:08:02,900
Joe.

1063
01:08:04,700 --> 01:08:06,500
How you holdin' up, partner?

1064
01:08:06,600 --> 01:08:09,900
David... is that you?

1065
01:08:11,000 --> 01:08:12,500
Yeah, pal, how you doin'?

1066
01:08:13,500 --> 01:08:16,300
It's bad. He's bad.

1067
01:08:16,400 --> 01:08:19,000
Didn't know anything
could hurt like this.

1068
01:08:20,000 --> 01:08:22,300
If you guys can't help me...

1069
01:08:23,500 --> 01:08:25,800
you... you gotta end it, okay?

1070
01:08:28,000 --> 01:08:30,400
Ollie's got that gun, right?

1071
01:08:31,900 --> 01:08:34,400
- Right?
- No. No way.

1072
01:08:34,500 --> 01:08:36,800
You can't fuck with me on this, bro.

1073
01:08:36,900 --> 01:08:39,099
Not with me like this.

1074
01:08:39,100 --> 01:08:40,600
I'll do it.

1075
01:08:40,700 --> 01:08:43,400
Just give me the gun.

1076
01:08:43,500 --> 01:08:45,100
Hey, hey. Shh.

1077
01:08:45,200 --> 01:08:48,300
- We're not there yet, okay?
- Oh, please!

1078
01:08:48,400 --> 01:08:50,100
Joe, now, listen.

1079
01:08:51,200 --> 01:08:54,399
Pal... we're gonna work something out.

1080
01:08:54,400 --> 01:08:57,300
I just need you to hang in
a little longer, okay? Can we do that?

1081
01:09:01,200 --> 01:09:02,900
Stay with him.
I'll be back.

1082
01:09:06,200 --> 01:09:10,200
Hattie, I need to go to the bathroom.
Will you watch Billy?

1083
01:09:12,100 --> 01:09:13,200
Hattie.

1084
01:09:29,800 --> 01:09:31,100
See anything?

1085
01:09:32,300 --> 01:09:35,200
The last of those bugs
went away about four.

1086
01:09:35,300 --> 01:09:38,400
Dawn's coming.
What's on your mind?

1087
01:09:38,500 --> 01:09:39,800
It's Joe.

1088
01:09:41,500 --> 01:09:44,600
We don't get him on some serious
antibiotics, he's gonna die of infection.

1089
01:09:44,700 --> 01:09:47,000
Plus he needs
painkillers in the worst way.

1090
01:09:47,100 --> 01:09:50,900
All... all... all we got here
is liquor and aspirin.

1091
01:09:51,000 --> 01:09:53,700
You... you thinkin' about goin'
to that pharmacy next door?

1092
01:09:53,800 --> 01:09:55,700
Irene Reppler says
they've got Silvadene...

1093
01:09:55,800 --> 01:09:57,600
you know, the stuff
they use in burn wards.

1094
01:09:57,700 --> 01:09:59,800
- She knows where they keep it.
- Slow down.

1095
01:09:59,900 --> 01:10:01,599
You can't actually
be thinkin' of doin' this.

1096
01:10:01,600 --> 01:10:03,599
I'm also thinkin' beyond that.

1097
01:10:03,600 --> 01:10:05,300
We have to get out of here.

1098
01:10:06,400 --> 01:10:09,800
- I mean <i>permanently.</i>
- Why? We got plenty to eat!

1099
01:10:09,900 --> 01:10:12,899
And what happens when one of those things
decides to break through this window?

1100
01:10:12,900 --> 01:10:15,700
I'm talkin' one of the big ones,
like the one that killed Norm.

1101
01:10:15,800 --> 01:10:18,700
Yeah, and that flaming torch idea
didn't work so well, did it?

1102
01:10:18,800 --> 01:10:20,800
We almost burned
the goddamn store down.

1103
01:10:27,100 --> 01:10:28,400
It's Hattie.

1104
01:10:35,200 --> 01:10:36,299
Here?

1105
01:10:36,300 --> 01:10:38,300
All right,
gently, now. Gently.

1106
01:10:38,400 --> 01:10:40,700
One... two... three.

1107
01:10:50,300 --> 01:10:52,500
I don't know
how long she was there like that,

1108
01:10:52,600 --> 01:10:53,900
lying there next to us.

1109
01:10:54,000 --> 01:10:55,700
I thought she was sleeping.

1110
01:10:57,100 --> 01:10:58,899
I got my four-wheel drive.

1111
01:10:58,900 --> 01:11:00,500
It's out there.

1112
01:11:00,600 --> 01:11:02,300
Y-you're talking about leaving?

1113
01:11:03,600 --> 01:11:05,100
Well, we...

1114
01:11:05,200 --> 01:11:07,000
should hit the pharmacy first.

1115
01:11:07,100 --> 01:11:08,676
We gotta bring back
supplies for the injured.

1116
01:11:08,700 --> 01:11:09,999
I mean, if we don't,

1117
01:11:10,000 --> 01:11:12,800
Joe Eagleton's gonna die,
and we can't let that happen.

1118
01:11:12,900 --> 01:11:14,000
But after that...

1119
01:11:15,000 --> 01:11:16,720
look, my Land Cruiser
can hold eight people.

1120
01:11:16,800 --> 01:11:19,000
I say we drive south
as far as the fuel takes us

1121
01:11:19,100 --> 01:11:21,300
and try to get clear of this mist.

1122
01:11:21,400 --> 01:11:23,400
That's it?

1123
01:11:23,500 --> 01:11:24,800
That's the plan?

1124
01:11:24,900 --> 01:11:26,800
- That's what I got.
- No, you can't mean it.

1125
01:11:26,900 --> 01:11:28,900
Not after what happened
to Norton and his group.

1126
01:11:29,000 --> 01:11:31,400
No, no, no. Amanda, <i>think.</i>

1127
01:11:31,500 --> 01:11:33,400
Norton got over 200 feet
from this store.

1128
01:11:33,500 --> 01:11:35,000
That's how much rope played out.

1129
01:11:35,100 --> 01:11:37,600
I'm parked half that distance from here.

1130
01:11:37,700 --> 01:11:39,699
But who knows how far
this mist has spread?

1131
01:11:39,700 --> 01:11:41,276
It could be the entire eastern seaboard.

1132
01:11:41,300 --> 01:11:43,500
Yeah, it could be the whole world,
for all we know.

1133
01:11:43,600 --> 01:11:46,800
Wouldn't make us any less dead,
now, would it?

1134
01:11:46,900 --> 01:11:48,800
We have one gun.

1135
01:11:48,900 --> 01:11:50,800
- How many rounds?
- We got ten left.

1136
01:11:50,900 --> 01:11:52,000
Ten rounds. Jesus.

1137
01:11:52,100 --> 01:11:53,800
Okay, so ten.

1138
01:11:54,800 --> 01:11:56,799
Want another reason
to get the hell out of here?

1139
01:11:56,800 --> 01:11:59,800
I'll give you the best one. Her.

1140
01:12:00,900 --> 01:12:02,400
Mrs. Carmody.

1141
01:12:02,500 --> 01:12:05,300
She's our very own Jim Jones.

1142
01:12:05,400 --> 01:12:08,100
I'd like to leave before people
start drinking the Kool-Aid.

1143
01:12:08,200 --> 01:12:09,200
He's right.

1144
01:12:09,300 --> 01:12:11,599
Flakier people get,
the better she's gonna look.

1145
01:12:11,600 --> 01:12:14,300
No, I don't buy that.
It's obvious she's nuts.

1146
01:12:14,400 --> 01:12:15,899
Look, a few people maybe, but...

1147
01:12:15,900 --> 01:12:18,200
No, I count four.
She's preachin' to 'em right now.

1148
01:12:18,300 --> 01:12:19,800
By noon, she'll have four more.

1149
01:12:19,900 --> 01:12:22,000
By tomorrow night,
when those things come back,

1150
01:12:22,100 --> 01:12:23,600
she'll have a congregation,

1151
01:12:23,700 --> 01:12:27,200
and then we can start worryin'
about who she's gonna sacrifice

1152
01:12:27,300 --> 01:12:28,900
to make it all better.

1153
01:12:29,000 --> 01:12:30,699
Hmm?

1154
01:12:30,700 --> 01:12:32,699
You, Amanda?

1155
01:12:32,700 --> 01:12:34,000
My little boy?

1156
01:12:34,100 --> 01:12:35,700
He's right.

1157
01:12:35,800 --> 01:12:37,900
You don't have much faith
in humanity, do you?

1158
01:12:38,900 --> 01:12:40,300
None whatsoever.

1159
01:12:40,400 --> 01:12:41,900
I can't accept that.

1160
01:12:42,000 --> 01:12:44,700
People are basically good, decent.

1161
01:12:44,800 --> 01:12:46,800
My God, David, we're a civilized society.

1162
01:12:46,900 --> 01:12:49,900
Sure, as long as the machines
are workin' and you can dial 9-1-1,

1163
01:12:50,000 --> 01:12:52,800
but you take those things away,
you throw people in the dark,

1164
01:12:52,900 --> 01:12:54,899
you scare the <i>shit</i> out of them,

1165
01:12:54,900 --> 01:12:56,800
no more <i>rules,</i>

1166
01:12:56,900 --> 01:12:58,800
you'll see how primitive they get.

1167
01:12:58,900 --> 01:13:04,199
You scare people badly enough,
you can get 'em to do anything.

1168
01:13:04,200 --> 01:13:07,800
They'll turn to whoever
promises a solution,

1169
01:13:07,900 --> 01:13:09,100
or <i>whatever.</i>

1170
01:13:09,200 --> 01:13:11,200
Ollie, please, back me up here.

1171
01:13:11,300 --> 01:13:13,000
I wish I could.

1172
01:13:13,100 --> 01:13:15,400
As a species,
we're fundamentally insane.

1173
01:13:16,400 --> 01:13:21,100
Put more than two of us in a room, we pick sides
and start dreaming up reasons to kill one another.

1174
01:13:22,100 --> 01:13:24,799
Why do you think we invented
politics and religion?

1175
01:13:24,800 --> 01:13:28,599
Oh, Jesus, that's just... wrong.

1176
01:13:28,600 --> 01:13:31,100
Look, nobody has
to decide anything now, okay?

1177
01:13:31,200 --> 01:13:34,400
First things first... the pharmacy.

1178
01:13:35,900 --> 01:13:37,599
That'll be our test run.

1179
01:13:37,600 --> 01:13:38,700
Okay?

1180
01:13:48,900 --> 01:13:50,699
It's all right, Big Bill.

1181
01:13:50,700 --> 01:13:52,400
I'm gonna bring you back
some comic books.

1182
01:13:52,500 --> 01:13:53,800
I don't want them.

1183
01:13:53,900 --> 01:13:55,500
I want you to stay here.

1184
01:13:55,600 --> 01:13:57,600
I won't be gone long.

1185
01:13:58,700 --> 01:14:00,700
Just... just next door.

1186
01:14:00,800 --> 01:14:02,600
Hey, you'll be safe.

1187
01:14:04,100 --> 01:14:05,200
Daddy...

1188
01:14:05,300 --> 01:14:06,800
Daddy, there are things out there.

1189
01:14:07,800 --> 01:14:09,600
Things...

1190
01:14:09,700 --> 01:14:12,600
Yeah. There's a lot
less of 'em in the daytime.

1191
01:14:14,200 --> 01:14:17,100
They'll wait. They'll wait in the mist
where you can't see 'em,

1192
01:14:17,200 --> 01:14:19,500
and then when you go
and can't get back in...

1193
01:14:19,600 --> 01:14:21,000
they'll come and eat you up!

1194
01:14:21,100 --> 01:14:23,400
- Shh.
- Daddy, don't go!

1195
01:14:32,700 --> 01:14:34,000
I'll be back.

1196
01:14:35,200 --> 01:14:37,800
Big Bill... I promise.

1197
01:14:37,900 --> 01:14:40,200
I'll be back, and then
I'm gonna take you home.

1198
01:14:41,300 --> 01:14:42,800
All right?

1199
01:14:42,900 --> 01:14:45,000
Together, we're going home.

1200
01:14:46,000 --> 01:14:49,299
If something happens,
anything at all, you cut and run.

1201
01:14:49,300 --> 01:14:52,000
You get your ass back in here,
for your boy's sake.

1202
01:14:52,100 --> 01:14:54,600
If something happens to me,
I want you to take care of Billy...

1203
01:14:55,600 --> 01:14:58,600
best as you can,
as long as you can.

1204
01:14:58,700 --> 01:15:00,400
Land Cruiser's yours now.

1205
01:15:01,500 --> 01:15:03,099
You... you get him out of here.

1206
01:15:03,100 --> 01:15:04,500
You just keep drivin'.

1207
01:15:11,100 --> 01:15:13,100
Where do you think you're going,
Mr. David Drayton?

1208
01:15:13,200 --> 01:15:16,199
Are you so anxious
to make your boy an orphan?

1209
01:15:16,200 --> 01:15:18,300
My boy is no concern of yours.

1210
01:15:18,400 --> 01:15:19,699
Listen up.

1211
01:15:19,700 --> 01:15:21,700
We're going to the pharmacy.

1212
01:15:21,800 --> 01:15:23,799
We're gonna bring back some supplies.

1213
01:15:23,800 --> 01:15:27,200
Also, there may be people
trapped over there who need help.

1214
01:15:27,300 --> 01:15:29,499
Listen, folks, listen!

1215
01:15:29,500 --> 01:15:31,500
We're not gonna take any chances.

1216
01:15:31,600 --> 01:15:33,099
If there's any trouble,

1217
01:15:33,100 --> 01:15:35,100
we'll come straight back here
to the supermarket.

1218
01:15:35,200 --> 01:15:38,599
And bring the fiends of hell
down on our heads, thank you.

1219
01:15:38,600 --> 01:15:40,100
She's right.

1220
01:15:40,200 --> 01:15:43,200
You'll make 'em notice us.
You'll make 'em come.

1221
01:15:44,200 --> 01:15:46,900
Why can't you just leave
well enough alone?

1222
01:15:47,000 --> 01:15:48,800
Lady, this what you call
"well enough"?

1223
01:15:48,900 --> 01:15:50,400
You wanna stop us?

1224
01:15:50,500 --> 01:15:52,000
You better explain to Bobby here

1225
01:15:52,100 --> 01:15:54,376
why we're not bringin' painkillers
and medicine back for his brother.

1226
01:15:54,400 --> 01:15:56,500
I'm goin', even if I have to go alone.

1227
01:15:56,600 --> 01:15:58,300
You'll die out there, young man.

1228
01:15:58,400 --> 01:16:01,499
You'll walk out that door
and be torn to shreds,

1229
01:16:01,500 --> 01:16:04,799
and then your hell-bound pride
will have them come get the rest of us.

1230
01:16:04,800 --> 01:16:07,600
Yes, they'll come back for all of us,
just like this good lady said.

1231
01:16:07,700 --> 01:16:09,700
Do you want that
to happen, people?

1232
01:16:09,800 --> 01:16:13,000
- No!
- No! No! No!

1233
01:16:13,100 --> 01:16:15,099
Well, it is this kind of hubris

1234
01:16:15,100 --> 01:16:17,600
that brought the wrath of God
in the first place.

1235
01:16:17,700 --> 01:16:19,300
This kind of pride and defiance of...

1236
01:16:21,100 --> 01:16:22,800
Shut up, you miserable buzzard!

1237
01:16:22,900 --> 01:16:24,100
You old bitch!

1238
01:16:24,200 --> 01:16:25,600
No, no, no, no!

1239
01:16:28,300 --> 01:16:31,400
Stoning people who piss you off
is perfectly okay.

1240
01:16:31,500 --> 01:16:33,100
They do it in the Bible, don't they?

1241
01:16:33,200 --> 01:16:35,000
And I got lots of peas.

1242
01:16:35,100 --> 01:16:37,700
David, please, if you want to go,
now's the time.

1243
01:16:37,800 --> 01:16:39,499
How 'bout it, Army?

1244
01:16:39,500 --> 01:16:41,000
Any help from the armed forces?

1245
01:16:41,100 --> 01:16:42,200
I'll go.

1246
01:16:44,600 --> 01:16:47,600
Jim Grondin.
I had you in school, didn't I?

1247
01:16:47,700 --> 01:16:49,700
Yes'm, me and my sister Pauline.

1248
01:16:49,800 --> 01:16:51,400
Pair of underachievers.

1249
01:16:51,500 --> 01:16:52,700
After you, Jim.

1250
01:16:53,800 --> 01:16:55,100
Yes, ma'am.

1251
01:16:55,200 --> 01:16:56,599
Oh, <i>shit.</i>

1252
01:16:56,600 --> 01:16:59,000
That it?
That's everybody?

1253
01:16:59,100 --> 01:17:00,600
Everybody that's goin'.

1254
01:17:00,700 --> 01:17:02,700
- Yep.
- Okay.

1255
01:17:02,800 --> 01:17:05,800
Single file,
one by one, all right?

1256
01:17:05,900 --> 01:17:07,600
Let's get this thing over with.

1257
01:17:08,800 --> 01:17:09,900
Let's go.

1258
01:17:10,000 --> 01:17:11,700
- After you.
- Yes.

1259
01:17:14,700 --> 01:17:15,700
Stay together.

1260
01:17:18,900 --> 01:17:20,700
- Get the door.
- You know what?

1261
01:17:20,800 --> 01:17:22,376
- Mrs. Carmody, you're not helping.
- I don't care.

1262
01:17:22,400 --> 01:17:24,100
- Shut the hell up!
- You shut up!

1263
01:17:30,900 --> 01:17:32,200
Save the batteries.

1264
01:18:19,700 --> 01:18:21,299
<i>Shit.</i>

1265
01:18:21,300 --> 01:18:23,300
They left the doors propped open.

1266
01:18:24,700 --> 01:18:26,200
Think something got in?

1267
01:18:27,700 --> 01:18:32,200
Let's just... get what we need,
get the hell outta here.

1268
01:18:32,300 --> 01:18:33,700
Yeah. Let's do that.

1269
01:18:33,800 --> 01:18:38,200
The meds are
over at the end there, in the cubicle.

1270
01:18:58,700 --> 01:19:02,100
- Will you not do that?
- I'm sorry. I'm <i>sorry.</i>

1271
01:19:02,200 --> 01:19:04,200
Oh, <i>Go d.</i>

1272
01:19:28,900 --> 01:19:30,199
Where's that Silvadene?

1273
01:19:30,200 --> 01:19:31,700
It's over behind David.

1274
01:19:31,800 --> 01:19:33,700
In the fridge. Check there.

1275
01:19:39,800 --> 01:19:41,300
